    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNvim 0.11-dev crashes with the following error\n\n```\nAssertion failed: (opt_idx != kOptInvalid), function get_option, file option.c, line 3399.\n```\n\nwhen accessing an option that does not exist. This is a regression since 29ded889579a9d590e8ea885a9a402ff4bae87be (#31066). /cc @famiu\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\n:lua vim.api.nvim_get_option('invalid')\n```\n\nTo my knowledge, this bug was first reported in https://github.com/neovim/pynvim/pull/584:\n```bash\nnvim --clean --headless -c \"py3 vim.current.buffer.options['invalid-option']\"\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nShould raise an error: `Invalid option name: 'invalid-option'`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11 commit 29ded8895\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nN/A\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from source",
